<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/454290-clearly-the-last-described-residence-hotel">Clearly the last described residence hotel in this novel strays into the realm of fantasy. Is there someone out there knowledgeable enough of turn of the Twentieth Century NY residence hotels to comment on just how far into the realm of fantasy it does stray?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_454290'><a id="like_count_community_question_454290" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/454290?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">1 like</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F146219.Martin_Dressler">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/454290-clearly-the-last-described-residence-hotel">6 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/454290-clearly-the-last-described-residence-hotel">See all 2 answers</a>
</li>
